-----BEGIN PLACEHOLDER-----
Replace this file with Safaricom's production CA chain before any
production deployment.

How to obtain:
  1. Log in to the Daraja portal as the SACCO's API admin.
  2. Settings → Security → "Download production CA bundle".
  3. Paste the contents here, preserving the BEGIN CERTIFICATE / END
     CERTIFICATE markers exactly as downloaded.
  4. Re-deploy the mpesa binary; the cert is embedded via go:embed
     at build time (see services/mpesa/internal/daraja/certs.go).

Until this file is replaced AND the embed in certs.go is flipped on,
the mpesa Client falls back to the system root CA store. That's safe
for sandbox traffic but a production deployment MUST pin against the
known-good Safaricom chain to defend against a hostile CA in the
node's system store.
-----END PLACEHOLDER-----
